The paper focuses on post-hoc explanations of machine learning models, which is a common topic in the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of counterfactual explanations also suggests a focus on interpretability and explainability, which are also common themes in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the feasibility and actionability of counterfactual explanations, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also addresses the tradeoffs and causal implications of optimizing for counterfactuals, which could fall under the subfield of cybersecurity (cs.CY) or cryptography (cs.CR).
